posts.com: When you listen to a lot of different avant-garde jazz releases, you have to mentally prepare yourself. You don't listen to Cecil Taylor or Albert Ayler as background music. You don't put "Interstellar Space" on and just go ahead and do the dishes. Free jazz, spiritual jazz, vanguard jazz, this is is music literally created to combat the passive and often dismissive nature of people wanting to "listen" to jazz. With a notion of jazz being for the beatniks and the coffee shops, the idea was struck down quickly by these very masters - finding new ground in the same way that many psychedelic rock bands were allowing hippies to reach higher astral planes.

Since you're bringing up that era, here's another idea.
Romania in the mid to late 19th century had a huge problem with peasants and the agricultural land.
A reform was made that gave peasants land. I won't go into all details, but some historians point out that this effectively kept Romania poor and rural for much longer, becasue it prevent the surplus peasants from moving to the cities and becoming workers or finding other types of jobs since they had the small plots of land to work now.

This also made Romanian agriculture inefficient due to fragmentation of lands.
It's one of the reasons why Romania stayed poor in the interwar era, WW2 and into communism.
It was a huge disadvantage for Romania

But I thought about something else.
That huge and poor rural population had a high birth rate. Industrialization and urbanization slows that down. These two processed happened much later in Romania, and only fully went into gear during communism. In fact, urbanization is still ongoing in Romania. It could have actually made the Romanian population bigger long term, compared to an early industrialization scenario.

I don't think the land reform was an important factor in that, judging by what happened in Russian Poland and Austrian Poland. In Russia the land reform (dividing noble estates and distributing the land among the peasants) happened in the 1860s, in Austria (Galicia) - in the 1840s. Yet in Russian Poland industry was developing well, while in Galicia - not really. You know, industry doesn't come out of thin air, it's not enough that you just have masses of poor people dwelling in big cities for the industry to kick off, that's why Brazil or Nigeria aren't major industrial hubs despite having enormous cities filled with poor people.

Industry had to be developed due to independent factors and then if salaries in the industry were high enough to attract peasants from villages, they would move to the cities (like it happened in Russian Poland, worth reading about development of Łódź) and if they weren't, then they would stay in their villages and starve or emigrate abroad (like it happened in Galicia)

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
>>176989844
>But I don't know how they all are related.
All come from the same proto-slavic root, coлдъ, meaning malt (which is sweet) In the east, ColC (coлдъ) turned into ColoC (coлoд), in the west into ClaC (slad). Compare "зoлтo -> зoлoтo / zlato" or with r instead of l: "гopдъ -> гopoд / hrad", "cтopнa -> cтopoнa / strana". Old Church Slavonic brought the western forms to the east, but usualy they have either a different meaning (cтpaнa) or are seen as archaic/poetic (гpaд, злaтo). I thought that would be the case here as well, but apparently the Old Curch Slavonic form was the one that caught on.

posts.com: Dans l'économie actuelle de Roblox, ce n'est pas vraiment une surprise. 100 robux sont l'équivalent d'un dollar et c'est bien connu. Vous devez également noter que l'économie de Roblox - bien que virtuelle - est tout comme une économie de la vie réelle. La valeur des robux peut fluctuer en fonction des valeurs capitalistes - les utilisateurs peuvent décider du prix de leurs produits et cela peut changer complètement la valeur des robux. Les articles vendus au début des années 2010 comparés aux articles vendus aujourd'hui en sont un bon exemple. Un chapeau moyen sur Roblox, avant l'UGC, en 2014, valait environ 15 à 20 robux, soit environ 0,5 à 1 dollar.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com: Si vous regardez un chapeau moyen aujourd'hui - qui est un article UGC - cet article coûterait 50-100 robux, ce qui est aussi toujours environ un dollar. Non seulement les décisions économiques de l'utilisateur sont un facteur important dans l'économie virtuelle, mais aussi les fluctuations économiques de la vie réelle. Même si l'économie des robux était bien maintenue, elle ne peut pas éviter les fluctuations du dollar américain ou d'autres monnaies de la vie réelle. 100 robux, ça peut paraître beaucoup, mais c'est la réalité de l'économie. Je veux dire, je suis personnellement d'accord que c'est beaucoup, et je blâme principalement la communauté Roblox pour être le principal problème dans ce domaine. Détruire l'économie en raison de leur cupidité et de leur inexpérience.

Sorry for the late reply.

>in "戦う時は、相手と傷つけ合います" と is used because of the 合います later, right?
Yes, exactly.

>皆、スマホを使いすぎているのではないでしょうか*
>why is は here incorrect? I want to say "everyone is using their smartphones too much, no?"
The 皆は itself is not grammatically incorrect, but it sounded a little bit weird to me when I saw the sentence.
But on second thought, I realized 皆は was not wrong in any way.
Sorry for confusing you.

>インターネットを使わなくても、人生はとても楽しいです*
should've mentioned that each of those sentences had to use a specific grammar bit, and in this one it was the "ずに". I thought I used it ok here.

I can't put my finger on it, but ずに can't be used in this case.
If you want to use it, then you've got to change the whole sentence just like
>インターネットを使わずに、人生を楽しむこともできます。
or
>インターネットを使わずに、楽しい人生を送ることもできます
or something like that.

>Would "ああいうアニメはもう作りませんでしょうか。"be alright?

No, ~ません necessarily has to be at the end of the sentence, so でしょうか can't be attached after it.
You need to say ああいうアニメはもう作らないのでしょうか instead.

>how do I make a good one with うちに?
There's nothing for it but to use うちは in place of うちに like:
>漫画と本があるうちは、幸せです.
However, it sounds kind of unnatural to me because it implies that manga and books are likely to be gone sooner or later, which is why I rephrased it as 限り.

>>176993600
A Finnish heritage disease is a genetic disease or disorder that is significantly more common in people whose ancestors were ethnic Finns, natives of Finland and Sweden (Meänmaa) and Russia (Karelia and Ingria). There are 36 rare diseases regarded as Finnish heritage diseases.[1] The diseases are not restricted to Finns; they are genetic diseases with far wider distribution in the world, but due to founder effects and genetic isolation they are more common in Finns.

Within Finland these diseases are more common in the east and north, consistent with their higher association with ethnic Finns than with ethnic Swedes.[2] The Finnish disease heritage does not extend to other ethnic groups in the region, the Sámi and Karelians other than Finnish Karelians. It is attributed to a population bottleneck among ancestors of modern Finns, estimated to have occurred about 4000 years ago, presumably when populations practicing agriculture and animal husbandry arrived in Finland.[3]

In Finland about one in five persons carries a gene defect associated with at least one Finnish heritage disease, and about one in 500 children born is affected.[4] Most of the gene defects are autosomal recessives, so that if both the mother and father carry the same defect, the chance that their child will have the associated disease is 1 in 4. The molecular genetics of many of these diseases have been determined, enabling genetic testing, prenatal testing, and counseling. This has raised questions of bioethics and eugenics.[5]

It's because the standard for garbage is lower. I am a complete weeb and have read a lot of manga and watched a lot of anime. The quality control and thus baseline quality for manga has plummeted dramatically ever since the rise of isekai. What this means is that for the medium as a whole is that the average quality has fallen off of the face of the earth, and you're left trying out 20 manga before you get just that single readable one. Manhwa/Webtoons on the other hand, well they never peak very high. The peaks of manga are overwhelmingly superior to Manhwa/Webtoons in every way, and there has not been one truly exceptional Webtoon/Manhwa I've read despite reading at least a few hundred by now. That being said, the average quality is simply superior to that of manga. Manhwa/Webtoons all clump together evenly between 3-8/10, whereas with manga it ends up being like nine 1's and one 10. This has caused many people to shifting to reading manhwa/webtoons once they get a taste for them. If you're a casual reader, you can keep reading the great manga and never have to start wading through the heaps of horseshit, but if you actively read it as a pass time, webtoons inevitably become the superior medium.

Ich hatte nie viele Freunde und war schon immer schüchtern. Habe früher viel gezockt und sonst keine Hobbies oder Interessen entwickelt und nie Sport gemacht. Das rächt sich inzwischen.

Bin vor 2 Jahren mehrere hundert Kilometer entfernt in einen anderen Teil Deutschlands gezogen zwecks Arbeit (ländliche Gegend). Kenne hier bis heute außerhalb der Arbeit absolut niemanden. Arbeitskollegen sind zwar nett aber hauptsächlich älter als ich und verheiratet mit Kindern. Ich würde gerne Freunde in meinem Alter finden. Hatte außerdem noch nie eine Freundin. Habe leider Sozialphobie und werde durch die Einsamkeit zunehmend depressiver.

Ich würde mein Leben sehr gerne ändern, da ich diese Situation kaum noch ertragen kann. Ich mache inzwischen regelmäßig Sport (Homeworkout & Joggen) und zocke kaum noch. Achte außerdem mehr auf mein Aussehen. Leider habe ich keine Ahnung wie ich Freunde oder eine Partnerin finden kann. Wohne in einer ländlichen Gegend. Ich überlege mich im Fitnessstudio anzumelden. Lernt man da Leute kennen? Ansonsten ist Sportverein natürlich die Standardantwort. Jedoch habe ich zuvor nie eine Sportart gemacht und bin unsicher ob ich da mit 28 reinkommen kann. Sozialphobie macht das Ganze auch nicht leichter aber ich arbeite dran und will mir einen Therapieplatz suchen.

Habt ihr irgendwelche Tipps wie ich in meiner Situation Freunde finden kann? Bin echt für alles zu haben. Aktuell bin ich jeden Abend und jedes Wochenende alleine. Was kann ich tun um mit Menschen in Kontakt zu kommen? Ehrenamt, Vereine, Stammtische? Was gibt es, wo man ohne Vorerfahrung noch Anschluß findet? Ich verzweifel langsam echt.
